<span id="freeTextContainer1982053063482312401">i’m in the minority (minority. heh heh.) in finding this book superior to ellison’s <i>invisible man</i>. it might not be as daring, might lack the touch of modernist irony, but sometimes ya gotta shove all that aside and recognize a great book for just being a great book. something ellison’s book just ain&apos;t.<br/><br/><br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText1982053063482312401" style="display:none">i’m in the minority (minority. heh heh.) in finding this book superior to ellison’s <i>invisible man</i>. it might not be as daring, might lack the touch of modernist irony, but sometimes ya gotta shove all that aside and recognize a great book for just being a great book. something ellison’s book just ain't.<br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
